<h1 id="toc7"><span>Captain Kirby IRL</span></h1>
<p><em>Disclaimer: Identifying Personal Information has been redacted for privacy and security concerns.</em></p>
<p>My name is [PERSONAL INFORMATION REDACTED] and I am a computer science major at [PERSONAL INFORMATION REDACTED]. I've been writing just stuff for years, and I've even self-published a novel (and will at some point self-publish a second one). However, I'm still quite the amateur. I'm probably best at writing comedies (like [<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3305">SCP-3305</a>]), but I've found myself attracted to writing horror. My first collection of horror stories that I enjoyed were by H.P. Lovecraft, who you should read if you haven't already.</p>
<p>I spend a lot of my free time doing robotics research and playing board games. I was part of a FIRST Robotics Team when I was in high school called [PERSONAL INFORMATION REDACTED]. I write entirely as a hobby, because I would like to build and program robots for a living. Sure, that may sound like a first grader's answer to &quot;what do you want to be when you grow up&quot;, but robots are still the goal.</p>
<p>Alright&#8230; that's all I'm going to tell strangers on the internet. I hope you like reading my stuff! It's kinda flattering that anyone would even click on this part of my author page in the first place.</p>
<p>Thanks again for be at all interested in what I have to say. Or write. Or&#8230; you get the point.</p>
</div>
